<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-60-0291 </DOCNO><TEXT>A group of international contributors explores the ways in which technologicaland political changes have affected the original concepts of nuclearwar and deterrence strategies, and how such changes have affected policyand doctrine. The contributors also outline realistic, alternative waysof thinking about strategy in the changing context of new military technologiesand international politics, including several thought-provoking discussionsof the new Strategic Defense Initiative.</TEXT></DOC>